{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-iso3166-blr"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Independent Public-Sector Market-Entry & Procurement Compliance Service — Republic of Belarus"
 :itonami.blueprint/iso3166 "BLR"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :public-sector/market-entry-compliance
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :market-entry-compliance-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics false
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MarketEntry-LLM sealed into a single :advise node, always routed through
 an independent Market-Entry Compliance Governor (src/marketentry/
 governor.cljc) and a 0->3 rollout-phase gate, via a langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (src/marketentry/operation.cljc) with an append-only audit
 ledger and a MemStore + DatomicStore (langchain.db via
 kotoba-lang/langchain-store) SSoT proven to satisfy the same store
 contract test. Governed operations: :engagement/intake,
 :jurisdiction/assess, :filing/draft, :filing/submit. Seven governor
 checks, all HARD (human-unoverridable): spec-basis citation,
 evidence-checklist completeness, restricted-supplier-list membership
 (flagship, Law No. 419-Z Art. 1/10), engagement-fee ground-truth
 recompute, UNP tax-registration verification (conditional on
 :requires-unp?), unfriendly-state-investor authorization (nationality-
 CONDITIONAL -- fires only when an engagement is itself flagged
 :from-designated-unfriendly-state?, narratively sourced from the US
 State Dept 2025 Belarus Investment Climate Statement, no fabricated
 decree number), plus double-draft/double-submit prevention. Belarus's
 own three-way institutional split (MART policy regulator + two
 separately-authorized e-procurement platform operators + a distinct
 business-registration authority) is modeled honestly with per-claim
 confidence levels in src/marketentry/facts.cljc. :filing/draft and
 :filing/submit never auto-commit at any phase; both the governor's
 high-stakes actuation gate and the phase gate agree independently."}
